<item>
            <title>[LU-8439] Explore use of permanent ssh connection in test framework</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8439</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently running ssh all the time for every minute command seems to add quite a bunch of extra time in our tests.&lt;br/&gt;
There&apos;s a hope that using permanent ssh connections is going to help it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Apparently openssh hs an option to reuse the connection too, but I am not sure if we can make it totally permanent or if we&apos;ll need to have one deliberately held background one to make that work,&lt;br/&gt;
but this needs to be tried and possibly made a standard part of the framework.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
